text: The Open International de Squash de Nantes 2015 is the 2015 edition of the Open International de Squash de Nantes, which is a tournament of the PSA World Tour event Challenger (Prize money: $10,000). The event took place at Le Lieu Unique in Nantes in France from 2 to 6 of September. Grégoire Marche won his first Open International de Nantes trophy, beating Henrik Mustonen in the final. Le Lieu Unique, venue of the 1st edition ==Prize money and ranking points== For 2015, the prize purse was $10,000.
